&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Inventory and Logistic Lead is responsible for the Shipping/Receiving function and Inventory Management functions for the company. This role will interact with many different teams, including engineering, production, facilities, mission management, and finance/accounting. The ideal candidate should be accustomed to working in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive inbound material. Verify receipts for compliance with accompanying transaction documentation (e.g., packing lists, invoices, purchase orders, etc.) and check for damage, quantity, correct part numbers, and revision levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review/inspect received material and verify for compliance with product certifications, specifications, and other requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Induct received material into inventory using cleanroom-appropriate labels, bins, drawers, racks, etc.; identifying part numbers and stored locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain proper inventory levels; include min/max stocking strategies where appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement a rigorous physical inventory cycle count process assuring continuous inventory accuracy and integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor shelf-life storage and maintain proper rotation of stock&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stage and disburse material, parts, kits, and subassemblies from inventory to support the needs of Production Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage shipping needs to ensure materials are handled, packaged, tracked and delivered as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the shipping/receiving import, export and global trade needs for the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, create, implement, and maintain key operational processes and KPIs supporting inventory and logistics excellence. Continuously identify opportunities for process improvement, implementing changes to enhance efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of all relevant receiving, inventory, shipping, and global trade documentation in the appropriate business systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the safe handling of all inventory items and material handling equipment (e.g., forklifts, pallet jacks, rolling racks, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required Skills and Experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ERP system experience (Oracle, SAP, NetSuite, or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in MS Office and SharePoint (or similar documentation tools)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible shift work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desired Skills and Experience:&lt;/p&gt;
